main event: A civilian observed an oval-shaped object over East Memphis, Tennessee on May 9, 1967.
interesting points: The object changed color from orange-red to a darker hue.
An extremely bright light appeared in the object, resembling the sun, and then disappeared.
The object was approximately the length of 6 cars.
The observer had seen similar objects on several occasions over different states in the eastern US and once over Nashville, Tennessee.
The observer was a college student with a keen interest in astronomy and outer space.
